docs.abstract: President Trump derided the city at the debate, and has depicted it as an “anarchist jurisdiction,” apparently in an effort to appeal to his base.
docs.snippet: President Trump derided the city at the debate, and has depicted it as an “anarchist jurisdiction,” apparently in an effort to appeal to his base.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the final weeks of the presidential race, President Trump cannot seem to stop harping on New York City.

headline.main: Why Trump Is Calling New York a Lawless ‘Ghost Town’
headline.print_headline: Hometown to ‘Ghost Town’: Trump Swipes at New York

docs.abstract: Older volunteers are reluctant to work during the pandemic. High school students, who are increasingly politically engaged and have more time, are taking their place.
docs.snippet: Older volunteers are reluctant to work during the pandemic. High school students, who are increasingly politically engaged and have more time, are taking their place.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — During the Wisconsin primary in April, Jacob Major, a high school student, noticed how the line for one of Milwaukee’s five polling locations dragged on for blocks. At the beginning of the pandemic, the city did not have enough volunteers and officials to staff its 180 polling sites, leading it to shutter 175 of them.

headline.main: With Polling Sites Lacking Workers, a New Generation Steps Up
headline.print_headline: With Older Poll Workers Wary, a New Generation Is Stepping In to Help

docs.abstract: Weary of tokenism, Black board members are now seeking institutional transformation.
docs.snippet: Weary of tokenism, Black board members are now seeking institutional transformation.
docs.lead_paragraph: For years, Black trustees at the country’s art museums have been talking to each other. They share their frustrations at being the only Black faces in board meetings. They exchange ideas about how to help recruit more Black directors, to collect more Black artists, to cultivate more Black curators.

headline.main: Black Trustees Join Forces to Make Art Museums More Diverse
headline.print_headline: Black Trustees Form Alliance  To Diversify Art Museums

docs.abstract: The move comes as President Trump promotes a false narrative of widespread voter fraud ahead of the election.
docs.snippet: The move comes as President Trump promotes a false narrative of widespread voter fraud ahead of the election.
docs.lead_paragraph: For decades, federal prosecutors have been told not to mount election fraud investigations in the final months before an election for fear they could depress voter turnout or erode confidence in the results. Now, the Justice Department has lifted that prohibition weeks before the presidential election.

headline.main: Justice Dept. Eases Election Fraud Inquiry Constraints as Trump Promotes False Narrative
headline.print_headline: Lifting Ban, Barr Pushes Inquiries Into Voter Fraud Before Election

docs.abstract: President Trump came to the debate ready with his regular wrap on race when asked to explain his description of “Black Lives Matter” as a symbol of hate: He claimed he had done more than any president since Abraham Lincoln for African-Americans, and he called himself the “least racist person in this room.” (Never mind that the moderator of the debate, Kristen Welker, is a Black woman.)

headline.main: Biden calls Trump ‘one of the most racist presidents we’ve had in modern history.’

docs.abstract: A monthslong dispute centers on the New York public broadcaster’s planned changes to its diversity council and its leader’s statement on racism.
docs.snippet: A monthslong dispute centers on the New York public broadcaster’s planned changes to its diversity council and its leader’s statement on racism.
docs.lead_paragraph: More than three dozen employees at the WNET Group, the parent company of New York’s public television stations, have called for the resignation of the longtime chief executive, Neal Shapiro, saying he had not done enough to improve working conditions for employees, especially those of color.

headline.main: 41 WNET Employees Call for Resignation of C.E.O. Neal Shapiro
headline.print_headline: WNET Employees Call for Resignation of Chief Amid Diversity Dispute

docs.abstract: Sanda Dia’s death after an initiation ritual was regarded as a tragic accident. Newly released videos and photos have made it a symbol of growing intolerance.
docs.snippet: Sanda Dia’s death after an initiation ritual was regarded as a tragic accident. Newly released videos and photos have made it a symbol of growing intolerance.
docs.lead_paragraph: GHENT, Belgium — Sanda Dia saw a fraternity as a doorway into a different life. The son of an immigrant factory worker, he was an ambitious 20-year-old Black student at one of Belgium’s most prestigious universities. The fraternity, Reuzegom, was home to the scions of Antwerp’s white elites.

headline.main: A Black Belgian Student Saw a White Fraternity as His Ticket. It Was His Death.
headline.print_headline: Hazing Death of Black Student Bares Racism’s Rise in Belgium

byline.original: By Matt Apuzzo and Steven Erlanger

docs.lead_paragraph: Back in the early 2000s, an academic named Robert Sampson did one of the better-known studies in urban sociology of the past 20 years, discreetly dropping thousands of stamped and addressed letters all over the streets of Chicago. What he was looking for, essentially, was to see which neighborhoods would be most diligent about dropping those letters in mailboxes rather than allowing them to collect footprints on the sidewalk and turn to pulp.

headline.main: The President Has Made Selfishness Our National Credo
headline.print_headline: Altruism and Moral Purpose by Jennifer Senior
